      "value": "<p>&gt;@UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.class-features.Item.BiLTxWD0s3JPqLHZ]{Gloom Gunner}</p>\n<p>As a standard action, you can spend 1 Resolve Point to make an attack against a creature you are aware of, ignoring all @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.rules.JournalEntry.Kjba2E3Ad5oMJ7hV.JournalEntryPage.1jkwbVTGQihSpCrL]{cover} and @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.rules.JournalEntry.Kjba2E3Ad5oMJ7hV.JournalEntryPage.nyB6pt2dd6iVQGmS]{concealment} (including total). If the attack is a ranged attack, the target must be within your weaponâ€™s first range increment. The attack affects only your selected target, even if it normally affects an area or multiple targets. You still have to roll to hit your target, and an attack that misses has no effect.</p>"
